00:06:14,633 --> 00:06:17,933
I log the start and end of the training.

122
00:06:18,566 --> 00:06:21,000
So I do that at the start,
and then at the end,

123
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:25,233
and then I exit with a clear status code,
say why did I shutdown?

124
00:06:25,233 --> 00:06:28,666
Which was that
sig, sig or sig term that I got.

125
00:06:29,633 --> 00:06:32,033
Pretty straightforward stuff

126
00:06:32,033 --> 00:06:32,633
okay.

127
00:06:32,633 --> 00:06:35,633
Node.js example very similar.

128
00:06:35,833 --> 00:06:38,633
I handle the sig int I call.

129
00:06:38,633 --> 00:06:41,633
I stop accepting any new connection
requests.

130
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:44,800
I let everything finish,
then I need to have finish.

131
00:06:45,066 --> 00:06:49,200
Then I force close
any remaining sockets at the deadline.

132
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:51,133
I close shared client.

133
00:06:51,133 --> 00:06:55,700
I close the shared clients
I have somewhere else

134
00:06:55,700 --> 00:06:59,033
after the server drain
and then I exit cleanly

135
00:06:59,466 --> 00:07:02,200
so everything goes through that shutdown

136
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:05,200
method that that I've, created there.

137
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:07,000
Okay,

138
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,033
one more example.

139
00:07:08,033 --> 00:07:10,000
Python example.

140
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:10,900
Same thing.

141
00:07:10,900 --> 00:07:13,966
I captured this Sigint,
which you can see here,

142
00:07:15,166 --> 00:07:16,600
capture the Sigint.

143
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:19,466
I marked the app as draining to reject

144
00:07:19,466 --> 00:07:22,466
any new work.

145
00:07:22,633 --> 00:07:22,900
Right.

146
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:25,900
I'm draining, my app.

147
00:07:26,133 --> 00:07:30,300
I finish any active request within
a timeout, so I put my timeout in there.

